 ```shell
 git clone https://github.com/lanxiang1017/GEM.git
 bash GEM/setup.sh
+conda activate gem
+```
+
+The updated `setup.sh` is tuned for Blackwell workstations such as RTX PRO 6000:
+- it creates a dedicated conda env with Python 3.10
+- it installs CUDA 12.8 inside that env via the NVIDIA conda channel
+- it installs PyTorch 2.7.0 with the official `cu128` wheels
+- it defaults GEM to `sdpa` attention instead of `flash_attention_2`
+
+Why `sdpa` instead of FlashAttention-4? This repository is wired around `flash_attention_2` today, while FlashAttention-4 is a separate package/API. On Blackwell, `sdpa` with recent PyTorch is the lower-risk path for both training and inference. If you later want to benchmark a different backend, you can override it with `GEM_ATTN_IMPL`.
+
+Optional knobs:
+- `GEM_ENV_NAME=my-gem bash GEM/setup.sh`
+- `GEM_INSTALL_TRAIN_DEPS=0 bash GEM/setup.sh` for inference-only setup
+- `GEM_INSTALL_BITSANDBYTES=1 bash GEM/setup.sh` if you specifically need 4-bit/8-bit loading
+
+Recommended verification after activation:
+
+```shell
+python -c "import torch; print(torch.__version__, torch.version.cuda); print(torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)); print(torch.cuda.get_device_capability(0))"
 ```
 
